      <h1 class="treasure-description__title">The Value of Consistent Design</h1>
      <h2 class="treasure-description__role">Author</h2>
      <p class="treasure-description__details">When someone visits a site for the first time, that’s a new experience. You can make the experience look and feel the same as others but, ultimately, it’s different because the core product is (hopefully) different. While I don’t believe in walking through the motions, the less a user has to learn during a new experience, the better.
      <br>
      <br>
      We should design with this in mind.
      </p>
